{"word":"H5516 - סִיסְרָא - Çîyçᵉrâʼ - see-ser-aw' - Sisera","slug":"H5516","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">סִיסְרָא</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Çîyçᵉrâʼ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>see-ser-aw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Sisera"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>סיסרא</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>sı̂yserâ'</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>see-ser-aw'</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Sisera = \"battle array\" <ol><li>the conquering general under king Jabin of Hazor and slain by Jael</li><li>ancestor of a family of temple slaves who returned from exile with Zerubbabel</li></ol> <p />Origin: of uncertain derivation <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Masculine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4536\">H4536</a>, <a href=\"#/H5503\">H5503</a>, <a href=\"#/H5504\">H5504</a>, <a href=\"#/H5505\">H5505</a>, <a href=\"#/H5506\">H5506</a>, <a href=\"#/H5507\">H5507</a>, <a href=\"#/H5508\">H5508</a>, <a href=\"#/H5510\">H5510</a>, <a href=\"#/H5511\">H5511</a>, <a href=\"#/H5512\">H5512</a>, <a href=\"#/H5513\">H5513</a>, <a href=\"#/H5514\">H5514</a>, <a href=\"#/H5515\">H5515</a>, <a href=\"#/H5517\">H5517</a>, <a href=\"#/H5518\">H5518</a>, <a href=\"#/H5522\">H5522</a>, <a href=\"#/H5524\">H5524</a>, <a href=\"#/H5525\">H5525</a>"}]}